The paper deals with the computational complexity of the Maximum Independent Set problem on various types of geometric graphs, which suggests that it belongs to the computational geometry (cs.CG) sub-category. The use of fine-grained complexity analysis and the mention of the strong exponential time hypothesis (SETH) also suggest that it could belong to the data structures (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), computational complexity (cs.CC), or graph theory (cs.GT) sub-categories.
